WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Green Lentils - 1/2 Cup
Red Lentils - 1/2 Cup
Quinoa - 1/2 Cup
Onion - 1
Garlic Cloves - 5
Celery - 1 Stalk
Oat Flake - 1 Cup
Brewers' Yeast - 1 tbsp
Tomato Paste - 2 tbsp
A Handful of Parsley &amp; Coriander

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:25.000
Whole-Wheat Flour - 2 tbsp
Olive Oil
Salt - 1 tbsp
Ground Black Pepper - 1/2 tbsp
Sumac - 1/2 tbsp
Paprika - 1 tbsp

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:31.000
Cook the green lentils with 2 cups
of water. Bring to a boil, then
lower thr heat and cover the pan.
When it's half-cooked
add the red lentils and cook
for about 15 minutes.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:39.000
Put the lentils in a large bowl.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Cook the quinoa with 1 Cup of water.
Bring to a boil, then lower the heat
and cover the pan.
Cook for about 15 minutes.

00:00:48.010 --> 00:00:52.010
Cut the onion, garlic and celery.

00:00:53.010 --> 00:00:57.010
Heat a pan with 2 tbsp of olive oil.

00:00:59.010 --> 00:01:02.010
Fry onion until lightly browned.

00:01:03.010 --> 00:01:06.010
Add the garlic and celery.

00:01:08.010 --> 00:01:11.010
Mix for about 2 minutes.

00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:16.010
Add to the bowl.

00:01:18.010 --> 00:01:22.010
Add the chopped parsley and coriander.

00:01:23.010 --> 00:01:27.010
Add the salt

00:01:29.010 --> 00:01:32.010
Add the sumac

00:01:34.010 --> 00:01:37.010
Add the paprika

00:01:39.010 --> 00:01:42.010
Add the black pepper

00:01:43.010 --> 00:01:47.010
Add the brewers' yeast

00:01:49.010 --> 00:01:52.010
Add the tomato paste

00:01:54.010 --> 00:01:57.010
Mix, cover and refrigerate for an hour.

00:01:58.010 --> 00:02:02.010
Make burgers, coat with flour

00:02:03.010 --> 00:02:06.010
Heat a pan with oil

00:02:08.011 --> 00:02:11.011
Fry on medium heat until browned.

00:02:23.010 --> 00:02:26.010
Bon appetit!

